{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix format string vulnerability in O-RAN fronthaul configuration printing\n\n### Summary\nA format string vulnerability was found in the O-RAN fronthaul configuration printing functions where user-controlled data was passed directly to printf as format strings. This could lead to crashes or information disclosure.\n\n### Changes\n- `radio/fhi_72/oran-config.c`: Fixed format string vulnerabilities in `print_fh_init_io_cfg()` and `print_fh_init()` functions by:\n  - Escaping `%s` format specifiers as `%%s` in multi-line format strings\n  - Adding null checks with empty string fallbacks for user-controlled data\n  - Ensuring user data cannot be interpreted as format specifiers\n\n### Reproduction\nThe vulnerability can be triggered when:\n1. User provides malicious configuration data for DPDK device names, BBDEV device names, or file prefixes\n2. The system attempts to print the configuration using the affected functions\n3. Malicious format specifiers in user data (like `%n`, `%x`) could cause memory corruption or information disclosure\n\nThis fix prevents the vulnerability by ensuring all user-controlled strings are properly escaped and null-checked before being passed to printf.\n"
}